Lastly, the evolving nature of cyber threats necessitates continuous research and development in AI-based
cyber security. As attackers become more sophisticated, it is crucial to stay ahead of emerging threats by
constantly updating and refining AI algorithms and models.
In conclusion, the integration of AI in organisational cyber security has the potential to significantly enhance an organization's ability to detect and respond to cyber threats. The research findings highlighted the
effectiveness of AI-based intrusion detection systems and AI-powered chatbots in healthcare. However,
there are still knowledge gaps that need to be addressed, including exploring the broader implications of AI
in different domains, evaluating scalability and performance, addressing ethical considerations and biases,
and staying ahead of emerging threats through continuous research and development. By addressing these
gaps, organizations can harness the full potential of AI to strengthen their cyber security posture and
protect their valuable assets.

